editorialNotes.standard: There’s only one thing easier than visiting the library: bringing it to you. Meet Libby, an app that lets you log in to your local library to access ebooks, audiobooks, and magazines, all for the reasonable price of free. Sign in, link your library card, and go—it’s that simple.
editorialNotes.short: ‣ For readers, Libby allows you to check out books from your local library—directly on your iPad.

editorialNotes.standard: Marvel Unlimited’s tagline is “Never stop reading comics.” And given the sheer amount of content in there, that’s entirely possible. It’s pretty tough to overstate the amount of content in Marvel Unlimited. New titles turn up every week, sometimes as soon as six months after they hit stores. That means fresh issues of Asgardians of the Galaxy, Runaways, and Immortal Hulk.
editorialNotes.short: Read Marvel faves from The Avengers to Star Wars with a single subscription.
